Cooccurrence analysis

Source: R/ec_cooccurrence.R
ec_cooc.Rd

Cooccurrence analysis.

Usage

ec_cooc(x, ...)

# S3 method for pa
ec_cooc(x, ...)

# S3 method for cooc_count
ec_cooc(x, nsit, ...)

ec_cooc_pairwise(x, ...)

# S3 method for pa
ec_cooc_pairwise(x, ...)

# S3 method for cooc_count
ec_cooc_pairwise(x, nsit, ...)

ec_cooc_species(x, ...)

# S3 method for pa
ec_cooc_species(x, ...)

# S3 method for cooc_count
ec_cooc_species(x, nsit, ...)

ec_cooc_global(x, ...)

# S3 method for pa
ec_cooc_global(x, ...)

# S3 method for cooc_count
ec_cooc_global(x, nsit, ...)

Arguments

x

object to be converted into an object class pa.

...

ignored.

nsit

number of sites.

Functions

  • ec_cooc_pairwise(): Return a matrix of cooccurrence metrics for pair of species.

  • ec_cooc_species(): Return a matrix of cooccurrence metrics for species.

  • ec_cooc_global(): Return a matrix of cooccurrence metrics for species.

Examples

mat0 <- matrix(0, 10, 10)
mat1 <- matrix(1, 10, 10)
matU <- rbind(cbind(mat1, mat0), cbind(mat0, mat1))
ec_cooc(ec_as_pa(matU))
